CATEGORIES:Sight & Sound Films
DESCRIPTION:A GREAT AWAKENING tells the true story of an unlikely friendsh
 ip between the Reverend George Whitefield and Benjamin Franklin that resu
 lted in one of the most defining moments in American history. With the co
 lonies on the brink of collapse\, the Reverend George Whitefield ignites 
 the first Great Awakening\, uniting an entire generation with his thunder
 ing and faithful sermons and proclamations of liberty. In a miraculous tu
 rn of events\, one of Whitefieldâs closest friends and greatest promoters
  becomes none other than Benjamin Franklin. With the nationâs freedom han
 ging in the balance\, the founders discover true liberty cannot only be w
 ritten into law - it must be awakened in the hearts of the people.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260404
DTSTAMP:20260404T030502Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260403
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Great Awakening (Theatrical Release)
